episodes.title: Dance Mode
episodes.plot: After Dad eats her last chip, Bingo is given three chances to put Mum and Dad in "Dance Mode" as payback. But the others can't resist taking Bingo's turns for her.

episodes.title: Hammerbarn
episodes.plot: On a trip to Hammerbarn, Bluey and Bingo create their own mini-homes side-by-side in the trolley. But Bluey quickly gets jealous of her neighbour, Bingo.

episodes.title: Featherwand
episodes.plot: Bluey and Mum are off to Chloe's party and Bingo isn't invited. But armed with a magic featherwand that makes things incredibly heavy, Bingo can now stop them leaving the house.

episodes.title: Squash
episodes.plot: When dad and Uncle Stripe play a game of squash, Bluey and Bingo are in control of their every move, and Bingo proves that big siblings don't always beat little siblings.

episodes.title: Hairdressers
episodes.plot: During a game of hairdressers, Bluey discovers that big-headed customer Dad has nits. To help treat them Bingo has to find her voice, while Bluey has to find her ears.

episodes.title: Stumpfest
episodes.plot: Dad and his mates hit the backyard, ready to rip up some tree stumps. But when Bluey and Bingo take over a stump as a nail salon, Dad finds he's got some negotiating to do.

episodes.title: Favourite Thing
episodes.plot: When Bluey accidentally makes Bingo upset playing a game at dinner, she will do anything to make her happy again - even changing the rules of the game. But nothing seems to work.

episodes.title: Daddy Dropoff
episodes.plot: Dad refuses to be late dropping off Bluey and Bingo at kindy and school, but the girls make Dad play so many games, they quickly derail his plan.

episodes.title: Bingo
episodes.plot: When Bluey has a playdate at Chloe's, Bingo must learn how to play by herself. But all the games she knows need more than one person. Luckily Dad has a problem that needs solving.

episodes.title: Rug Island
episodes.plot: On Bingo and Bluey's Rug Island, a pack of felt pens can be anything: bananas, campfires, even a snake. But Dad will need to embrace his inner kid if he wants to make it his home.

episodes.title: Charades
episodes.plot: Bluey and Bingo want everyone to play charades, but Muffin and Socks are too young to understand the rules and Nana must think quickly to keep the game on track.

episodes.title: Sticky Gecko
episodes.plot: Chilli is taking Bluey and Bingo to the park to play with Judo, but they can't leave before they finish their game - waiting for a sticky rubber gecko to drop from the ceiling.

episodes.title: Dad Baby
episodes.plot: When Dad shows the kids how to use their old baby-harness, a new game is born: Dad Baby. But dad is unprepared for the harsh realities of giving birth to a baby Bingo.

episodes.title: Mum School
episodes.plot: Bluey plays mum to a brood of bouncy balloons, including an irrepressible floater named Greenie. But she soon discovers that mothering is much harder than she imagined.

episodes.title: Trains
episodes.plot: All aboard the Dad Train. Bingo goes from home to daycare to her job at the vet every morning, but there's trouble on the line as a mischievous Bluey throws everyone off schedule.

episodes.title: Army
episodes.plot: Jack is the new dog at school and the newest recruit in Rusty's Army. Jack struggles with following instructions and always forgets his hat, but Rusty will make a soldier of him yet.

episodes.title: Fancy Restaurant
episodes.plot: Bingo and Bluey want mum and dad to smoochy kiss, so they set up a romantic evening for two at their fancy restaurant. Everything goes to plan, until chef Bingo's special arrives.

episodes.title: Piggyback
episodes.plot: The Heelers take a long riverside walk, but Bingo's legs are tired, and she wants a piggyback. To distract her, mum and dad invent fun games and get her little legs moving again.

episodes.title: The Show
episodes.plot: When Bingo drops Mum's breakfast-in-bed on the floor, she's convinced she's ruined her big day. But Bluey helps make amends by putting on a play of how Mum and Dad first met.

episodes.title: Tickle Crabs
episodes.plot: When Dad brings a pair of tenacious tickle crabs home from the beach, nowhere in the house is safe. His only hope of escaping their tickles is with help from his true love.

episodes.title: Escape
episodes.plot: When Mum and Dad describe a made-up world where they can relax without the girls, Bluey and Bingo decide to burst into their fantasy and chase them down. How will Mum and Dad escape?

episodes.title: Bus
episodes.plot: During a game of bus, passenger Mum is too scared to tell bus driver Dad that she secretly loves him, until she gets some help from the Grannies

episodes.title: Queens
episodes.plot: During a game of Queens, Bluey and Bingo find that playing the butler is much more fun. But someone must play the queen, even if it means not being afraid of a bit of hard work.

episodes.title: Flat Pack
episodes.plot: While Mum and Dad struggle to build new flat-pack furniture, Bluey and Bingo transform the empty boxes into their own new world.

episodes.title: Helicopter
episodes.plot: At school, Bluey and her friends turn a tree stump into a thrilling game of Helicopter. But as the pilot, Bluey has to learn to give up some control, so they can all have fun.

episodes.title: Sleepytime
episodes.plot: Inside Bingo's dream, Bingo and Floppy have an intergalactic adventure, while the rest of her sleep-deprived family try to navigate Bingo's non-stop night-time bedhopping.

episodes.title: Grandad
episodes.plot: Grandad is supposed to be resting, but when Bluey and Bingo go to visit him, he makes a run for it with the kids and takes them on a madcap adventure into the bush.

episodes.title: Seesaw
episodes.plot: Dad has rudely plonked himself on one end of the seesaw. So Bluey and Bingo round up the entire playground to help flip him off, but they still need to find one more friend.

episodes.title: Movies
episodes.plot: It is Bluey's first trip to the cinema, but she's worried that the movie will be too scary. When Bingo starts running amok in the theatre, she must conquer her fear and help Dad out.

episodes.title: Library
episodes.plot: When Muffin is told that she is special by her Dad, she interprets it as an excuse to do anything she wants, which means playing Bluey and Bingo's game of Library her way.

episodes.title: Barky Boats
episodes.plot: Bluey and Mackenzie are excited to spend time with their two buddies Mia and Captain. When the older kids run off to play together without them, Calypso explains that growing up can be hard.

episodes.title: Burger Shop
episodes.plot: It's time for Bluey and Bingo to get out of the bath. But Dad has decided not to tell them what to do and gets roped into a game of Burger Shop.

episodes.title: Circus
episodes.plot: Bluey is the ringmaster in a game of circus with her friends, but Hercules wants to play his motorcycle game instead. Luckily Bluey has a solution to keep everyone happy.

episodes.title: Swim School
episodes.plot: Mum, Dad and Bingo must complete both their classes to pass Swim School but pleasing strict Big Fish instructor Margaret (aka Bluey) is proving very difficult.

episodes.title: Cafe
episodes.plot: In the park Bluey meets a new playmate Winnie, but when Bluey wants to invite her and her dad home for breakfast, she learns that adults take a little bit longer to make friends.

episodes.title: Postman
episodes.plot: When Mum and Dad have a disagreement, Bluey makes Dad write a love letter to Mum to make up. Now Bluey must find a way to play Ground's Lava with Bingo and deliver the letter to Mum, without squabbling.

episodes.title: The Quiet Game
episodes.plot: Bluey and Bingo are playing The Quiet Game and won't use words to tell Dad which toy to buy for Muffin. At his wit's end, Dad recruits new store clerk Alfie to help interpret the girls' miming.

episodes.title: Mr Monkeyjocks
episodes.plot: Dad thinks the kids have too many toys and suggests a chuck out. To save their beloved Mr Monkeyjocks from getting the chop, Bluey and Bingo must prove he is special.

episodes.title: Double Babysitter
episodes.plot: When Uncle Rad and Frisky accidentally turn up to babysit Bluey and Bingo on the same night, they have to work together to make Bluey feel better about babysitter put-downs.

episodes.title: Bad Mood
episodes.plot: Bingo is playing 'Bad Mood' with Dad, standing on his feet as Dad stomps around the house, controlling everything Bingo does and causing chaos. But how will Bluey get her to snap out of it?

episodes.title: Octopus
episodes.plot: When Chloe tries to teach her dad to improvise and play Bluey's game of Octopus, he finds it hard to understand or enjoy, until they both realise they can play it their own way.

episodes.title: Bin Night
episodes.plot: Bluey, Bingo and Dad always take the bins out. Over a few weeks, Bingo tells dad about a new kid at kindy who is mean to her and Mum offers some good advice.

episodes.title: Muffin Cone
episodes.plot: When Muffin can't stop sucking her thumb, she has to start wearing a cone of shame. But the cone gets in her way and can no longer play 'sandwich shop' with Bluey and Bingo.

episodes.title: Duck Cake
episodes.plot: Bluey wants to help make Bingo's birthday cake but first must put away her toys. But nothing can tempt her to clean up until Dad drops the cake.

episodes.title: Handstand
episodes.plot: At a party, Bingo is desperate to show off her handstand skills, while Nanna can't find a way to make herself useful. They're both feelings bit lost, until they find each other.

episodes.title: Road Trip
episodes.plot: Mum helps Bluey and Bingo find ways to entertain themselves on a family road trip, while dad tries to stay ahead of the grey nomad convoy or risk camping near the toilets.

episodes.title: Ice Cream
episodes.plot: Bluey and Bingo want a lick of each other's ice cream, but they are so focused on making sure each lick is fair, they don't notice their ice creams are melting.

episodes.title: Dunny
episodes.plot: Mum bans the girls from saying the word 'dunny' because it's not a word The Queen would use, but the kids try and trick her into saying it anyway.

episodes.title: Typewriter
episodes.plot: Bluey, Snickers and Winton are on their way to ask Calypso for help with their problems, when they are ambushed by the Terriers and use their unique talents to get past.

episodes.title: Baby Race
episodes.plot: Mum reminisces about Bluey and Judo as babies. Bluey learnt to roll over first, but Judo was the first to crawl, so then it became a race to see who would walk first.

episodes.title: Christmas Swim
episodes.plot: The Heelers gather for a classic Aussie Christmas, Bluey gets a new teddy and introduces him to the whole family. But the family play too rough with him and now he wants to go home. Until Frisky convinces him to stay.

episodes.title: Easter
episodes.plot: Bingo is convinced the Easter Bunny has forgotten them like last year, until Bluey finds a series of clues that leads them on an Easter egg treasure hunt.
